mil.nga.giat.geowave.ingest

Interface IngestTypePluginProviderSpi<I,O>

  • Type Parameters:
    I - The type for intermediate data
    O - The type for the resulting data that is ingested into GeoWave
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    GeoLifeIngestType, GeoToolsRasterDataStoreIngestType, GeoToolsVectorDataStoreIngestType, GpxIngestType, TdriveIngestType

    public interface IngestTypePluginProviderSpi<I,O>
    This interface can be injected and automatically discovered using SPI to provide a new ingest type to the GeoWave ingestion framework. It is not required that a new ingest type implement all of the plugins. However, each plugin directly corresponds to a user selected operation and only the plugins that are supported will result in usable operations.

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      IngestFromHdfsPlugin<I,O> getIngestFromHdfsPlugin()
      This plugin will be used by the ingestion framework to read data from HDFS in the form of the intermediate data format, and translate the intermediate data into the data entries that will be written in GeoWave.
      String getIngestTypeDescription()
      This is a user-friendly full description of the data type that this plugin provider supports.
      String getIngestTypeName()
      This will represent the name for the type that is registered with the ingest framework and presented as a data type option via the commandline.
      LocalFileIngestPlugin<O> getLocalFileIngestPlugin()
      This plugin will be used by the ingestion framework to read data from a local file system, and translate supported files into the data entries that will be written directly in GeoWave.
      StageToHdfsPlugin<I> getStageToHdfsPlugin()
      This plugin will be used by the ingestion framework to stage intermediate data to HDFS from a local filesystem.

      • getIngestTypeName

        String getIngestTypeName()
        This will represent the name for the type that is registered with the ingest framework and presented as a data type option via the commandline. For consistency, this name is preferably lower-case and without spaces, and should uniquely identify the data type as much as possible.
        Returns:
        The name that will be associated with this type

      • getIngestTypeDescription

        String getIngestTypeDescription()
        This is a user-friendly full description of the data type that this plugin provider supports. It will be presented to the command-line user as help when the registered data types are listed.
        Returns:
        The user-friendly full description for this data type
